citalopram help i have been prescribed citalopram for panic attacks and anxiety problems the problem is since taking the drug i am constantly tired and spend so much time sleeping has anyone else found this happens when taking citalopram it is getting me down and i am trying so hard to resist sleeping through the day but it is too hard hi laura i was on citalopram for a total of months in two different periods i didn't experience any sleepiness the only side effect i had was a total lack of sex drive it made me feel good as a general rule though if the sleepiness is really bad and you aren't getting any benefit otherwise then you should see your doctor he might change your dose or put you on something else but it might be a temporary side effect i started taking amitriptyline in february and it knocked me out at first now i am totally used to it and it doesn't make me tired at all unfortunately this sort of medication affects everyone differently so it's best to go back to your doctor and tell him what you're experiencing so he can make an informed decision about making your medication more effective for you good luck Citalopram Prostate cancer Selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor Clinical depression Chronic fatigue syndrome Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Antidepressant Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Stomach cancer Anxiety Sleep Bipolar disorder Narcolepsy Urinary incontinence Psoriasis Antiretroviral drug Paroxetine Epilepsy Fibromyalgia Tianeptine Migraine Diazepam Social rule Unemployment Antipsychotic COX-2 inhibitor Panic attack Clomipramine Methamphetamine Multiple sclerosis LSD Maprotiline Procrastination Insomnia Venlafaxine Isotretinoin Malaria Parkinson's disease Cannabis (drug) Sin City Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Project MKULTRA Star Wars: Galaxies Transsexuality Theory of conduct Anxiolytic Expert system Hypnosis The Contender (television series) Medical prescription One Tree Hill (TV series) Tricyclic antidepressant Human adaptation to spac